Unfortunately, you can\'t change the ROM on the fly! This app will now quit. Please restart it to take ROM change into account !
Tweak to improve perf at expense of compatibility
ARM optimized core (No save states, needs App Restart!)

New in v1.13:

- Disabled auto frameskip (not working anymore). Set the default frameskip value to 1.
- Fixed multitouch joystick.
- Better mouse implementation (still far from perfect): better screen matching and you can now pair VOL+ and VOL- for left and right click.

New in v1.12:

- A few fixes.
- Revert floppy speed to 100% and added a setting for it.

New in v1.11:

- New core based on uae4all2: AGA and Amiga 1200 Support. YOUR PREVIOUS SAVE STATES ARE NOT COMPATIBLE WITH THIS NEW ONE, SORRY :(
- HD files (.hdf) and dirs support (didn't really tested the HD dir support, just tell me).
- New settings for memory sizes, chipset, model, etc.
- Amiga Forever ROMs support (New rom key setting).
- Removed the old cyclone core.

New in v0.998:

- Fixed menu button disappearing with some devices.
- Fixed potential failures when loading save states.

New in v0.997:

- Orientation support
- Small key mapping changes, you may have to reconfigure them !
- SHIFT and ARROW keys are now available, both for physical mapping and displayed in the virtual keyboard alt section (the up arrow next to 'Z').
- Virtual keyboard is now multitouch, so let's say pinball games are now quite enjoyable in portrait mode :).

New in v0.996:

- Added SPACE mapping in physical controls section.
- Fixed RETURN key on virtual keyboard.
- Fixed inverted downleft/downright.
- MIPS support.

New in v0.995:

- Small maintenance update.
- x86 Support !.
- Alternate "input method" option for bluetooth connectivity.
- Two players support (Physical controls via Bluetooth).
- Screen always on when amiga is running.

New in v0.99:

- Better multitouch controls.
- Cyclone core not the default one anymore.
- Screen size option.
- Floppy removal.

New in v0.98.1:

- Mouse clicks on physical keys
- Revert regression on 1.5 devices and ROM issues on Cyclone Core?

New in v0.97:

- Optional new CPU core + save states. ARM Cyclone Core still enabled by default because it's faster. Your choice (I hope to manage save states on Cyclone one day).

- Different graphic management: No more relying on OpenGL for framebuffer support : too much performance differences between devices

- Right mouse support

- Fire with trackball by default

- NTSC support

- FPS/Drive loading status bar
Careful, only working with 2 bluetooth controllers (need restart !)
